The time has come for me to give those final huggies and retire Merlina Drakurion...(and a slew of others with her)<br>
<br>
I promised an explanation to a lot of you, so heres the jist of it. <br>
<br>
As many of you know there has been a bug as of late that is allowing duplicate usage of my name - VI says its fixed but after they said it was, yet another was created - shown me while online then deleted (just goes to show ya VI's worth, I guess /sigh)<br>
<br>
Secondly, for a long time I have been putting up with not so nice tells due to another player with a similiar name who is apparently accustomed to being an ass to other players - which results in my getting some off colored tells more often than I care to think about. Granted after they realize I am not that person, they are appologetic and usually very nice - but I have lived with these &quot;sorts&quot; of mistells for over a year and its getting old. I did ask VI to change MY name, and they have refused - reason given is &quot;you are a level  60 and we will not change your name&quot; /sigh  Nor have they been able to correct this problem for the duration...Thier refusal to solve the problems just made me sit down and wonder why the hell am I paying them for 5 accounts when they refuse to assist in something correctable with changing ONE name - thus I am done paying them.<br>
<br>
With Merlina, I have been basically involved with 3 guilds over my approximate 2 years here on lanys.  First my own guild Chaotic Senate (we were all babies, lol, but it was a blast). Second was Soul Assassins - I went at Lann's request and that was a learning experience - there I met some of the best players I have ever known in EQ and one remains especially dear to my heart. The last was CS/7D - here I have not only had EQ friends - but RL friendships, and I know these will continue. All said and done - I wouldn't change much of anything - except seeing them deteriorate the way they all did. The fighting / hurt feelings broke my heart, as it did many others.<br>
<br>
Lastly - RL problems have become pressingly complicated.  I came to EQ to get away from that - have good hearted fun and see so very many of you that I not only call friend, but truly family, and loved ones.  Sadly, EQ is no longer that escape for me... the politics and fights over loot ect have become torrid at times - thats not what this game is supposed to be for...<br>
<br>
So today, I stripped Merlina and laid her to rest (she looks like a noob, but that really doesn't matter now).  I am not going to name names here - jeesh it would take me a week to name off everyone that has touched my heart, made me smile,  blush <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , giggle, laugh so hard my sides ached, or jokingly exchanged /rudes with until noobs thought we would surely go to blows then we would hug and really startle them.  <br>
<br>
Such wonderful memories - I thank you all for each of them. Just know I  will remember each of you with a fondness that shall never fade.<br>
<br>
Many of you have my email addy ect to keep in touch (as we already do  /grin) if anyone wants to know how to get in contact with me, leave a post here and I will follow up.<br>
<br>
Most of all - keep that grin on your faces, sneak huggies when ya need em - and remember - its friendships that make things work - in RL, in EQ, in any realm - not the loot - it can't keep ya warm at night, nor can it hug ya when you are feeling blue.  Put the people first - not the items.<br>
<br>
Much love to you all /huggies<br>
<br>
Merlina Drakurion<br>
